formatTodo distinguishes empty vs clean: if no specs and no markers exist, it returns "Nothing to check: no specs or markers registered." with guidance. If synced, it returns "No changes detected. N specs, M markers, K edges in sync." Otherwise it prints summary counts bucketed by kind (edge drift, cascade drift, new edge(s), removed edge(s), broken edge(s)), then lists each todo with a kind-specific format. Direct-edge todos (TodoEdgeDrift without SourceSpecID) show From/To file locations, drift reason, and reset command; chain-drift todos (TodoEdgeDrift with SourceSpecID) show the affected spec and the source spec; cascade todos show the marker and source spec; edge-added/removed/broken todos show the edge endpoints and the appropriate reset command. The todo command exits 0 when clean (all linked + in sync), 1 when drift exists or unlinked markers are present, 2 on error. See principles.friction and unlinked_warning.